snippet: A Libyan court ordered Mustafa Abdel Jalil, a former political leader of rebels who toppled Col. Muammar el-Qaddafi last year, to be questioned in the killing of the insurgents’ top field commander, Gen. Abdel Fattah Younes.
abstract: Libyan court orders Mustafa Abdel Jalil, former political leader of rebels who toppled Col Muammar el-Qaddafi, to be questioned by military prosecutors in killing of insurgents' top field commander Gen Abdel Fattah Younes.
lead_paragraph: A Libyan court ordered Mustafa Abdel Jalil, a former political leader of rebels who toppled Col. Muammar el-Qaddafi last year, to be questioned in the killing of the insurgents’ top field commander, Gen. Abdel Fattah Younes.
